<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870413-0141 </DOCNO><HL> Coast Sandamp;L Thrift PurchaseGets Bank Board Approval</HL><DD> 04/13/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> CSA GOVMTTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   The Federal Home Loan Bank Board said it approved Coast Savings andamp; Loan Association's acquisition of San Diego-based Central Savings andamp; Loan Association, which has been run by federal regulators since May 1985.    The Federal Savings andamp; Loan Insurance Corp. will make a capital contribution, provide capital loss coverage and indemnify Coast against undisclosed liabilities and litigation that might stem from the transaction, the Bank Board said. A Bank Board spokesman declined to elaborate.    Central Savings, which operates 46 branches in California, has assets of $1.7 billion. Los Angeles-based Coast, which operates 93 savings branches and 13 regional lending centers in California, has assets of $9.2 billion, the Bank Board said. </TEXT></DOC>